                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13457845" author="thyzz" created="Tue, 18 Sep 2012 14:15:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;test runs on port 8080&lt;br/&gt;
test14 runs on port 8081&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13460030" author="aaron.j.garcia" created="Thu, 20 Sep 2012 22:57:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m also having this issue, but I went from 1.5.8 -&amp;gt; 6.0.0.  I have a Quick Start too, which I will attach.  It seems that this only happens when the RadioChoice form component is inside of a form.  When I had a RadioChoice component outside of the form, the issue wasn&apos;t occurring.  &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13460031" author="aaron.j.garcia" created="Thu, 20 Sep 2012 22:58:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Another quick start that illustrates the issue. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13460035" author="aaron.j.garcia" created="Thu, 20 Sep 2012 23:02:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Some more details (sorry for the multiple comments):&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Java Version: 1.7.0_04&lt;br/&gt;
Tomcat Version: 7.0.27&lt;br/&gt;
Firefox Version: 15.0&lt;br/&gt;
Operating System: Open Suse 11.4&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13460284" author="thyzz" created="Fri, 21 Sep 2012 06:45:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In my example the radio is inside a radiogroup, not in a form.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13467645" author="thyzz" created="Tue, 2 Oct 2012 12:25:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I build wicket from source, but the example provided in test.zip (and so also my application) still don&apos;t work. Can this be reopened?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13467680" author="mgrigorov" created="Tue, 2 Oct 2012 12:49:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;When I debugged it I used radio-choice-bug-6.0.0.tar...&lt;br/&gt;
Testing with test.zip I see that it fires the Ajax event twice - the second time it comes after repainting the group.&lt;br/&gt;
By just commenting out the line: &lt;br/&gt;
target.add(group); &lt;br/&gt;
in TestPage it starts working.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have no idea why it fires &apos;click&apos; event after the DOM replacements.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13467693" author="thyzz" created="Tue, 2 Oct 2012 13:03:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I wish I could comment out that line in my reallife application. There it&apos;s part of a larger repaint action.&lt;br/&gt;
I&apos;ll start digging, to see if I can find out why it gets repainted a second time.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13467700" author="thyzz" created="Tue, 2 Oct 2012 13:14:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;When I comment out target.add(group); it still fires the ajax call twice. &lt;br/&gt;
Only difference is that now the selection stay&apos;s&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13467917" author="thyzz" created="Tue, 2 Oct 2012 18:07:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The repainting of the dom doesn&apos;t trigger the second event.&lt;br/&gt;
When you click on the label 2 click events are fired. If you click on the radio button there is only one event.&lt;br/&gt;
See the attached html file demonstrating the issue. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This causes the ajax request to happen twice, with all kinds of weird side effects. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;some extra info: &lt;a href=&quot;http://bugs.jquery.com/ticket/10673&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://bugs.jquery.com/ticket/10673&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13467951" author="mgrigorov" created="Tue, 2 Oct 2012 18:38:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It is not the same. In your code the &amp;lt;label&amp;gt; doesn&apos;t wrap the &amp;lt;input&amp;gt;.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://jsfiddle.net/HKGsT/14/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://jsfiddle.net/HKGsT/14/&lt;/a&gt; works as expected.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13467968" author="thyzz" created="Tue, 2 Oct 2012 18:56:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ah yes. But as sone as you pull the click event to an wrapping div: &lt;a href=&quot;http://jsfiddle.net/LmMuy/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://jsfiddle.net/LmMuy/&lt;/a&gt; (which is basically the same as my earlier example) it gives the same behavior of the double event.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(May be I&apos;m now stating the obvious, not sure I understood your comment completely)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13467969" author="mgrigorov" created="Tue, 2 Oct 2012 18:56:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I just committed a change &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; which I&apos;ll have to revert :-/&lt;br/&gt;
It works only if the choice component is repainted with the Ajax response.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;1. &lt;a href=&quot;https://git-wip-us.apache.org/repos/asf/wicket/repo?p=wicket.git;a=commitdiff;h=881d03ec84ead3386d37faf0eecf50d05fe30ac9&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://git-wip-us.apache.org/repos/asf/wicket/repo?p=wicket.git;a=commitdiff;h=881d03ec84ead3386d37faf0eecf50d05fe30ac9&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13467992" author="mgrigorov" created="Tue, 2 Oct 2012 19:18:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think I solved it.&lt;br/&gt;
Please try the latest code in master branch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13467993" author="svenmeier" created="Tue, 2 Oct 2012 19:21:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have a solution for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/WICKET-4797&quot; title=&quot;CheckBoxMultipleChoice loses state&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;WICKET-4797&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;WICKET-4797&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; ready that would solve this issue too. May I interrupt your check-ins for a moment?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13468002" author="thyzz" created="Tue, 2 Oct 2012 19:29:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The test case (as in test.zip) works!!&lt;br/&gt;
Tomorrow, when I&apos;m actually working, i&apos;ll try the big app where I found the issue. Thanks so far&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13468048" author="svenmeier" created="Tue, 2 Oct 2012 20:42:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve checked a solution for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/WICKET-4797&quot; title=&quot;CheckBoxMultipleChoice loses state&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;WICKET-4797&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;WICKET-4797&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; which addresses this issue too. Now the input name is used for Ajax precondition and identification of checked inputs, which hopefully is much simpler to understand and maintain.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I took the opportunity to impoved  the Javascript similar Carl-Eric&apos;s AbstractCheckSelector.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13468389" author="thyzz" created="Wed, 3 Oct 2012 07:34:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It works! Thanks Martin and Sven&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
